Edo State government has cancelled the 10 days break declared for public and private schools following the postponement of the National Sports Festival (NSF) initially scheduled for March 22. Commissioner for Education Jimoh Ijegbai, in a statement on Tuesday, said schools have been asked to reopen following the postponed NSF. According to him, public and private schools are to follow the original school calendar so that the second term vacation would start by April 3. He noted that the third term resumption remained April 27 as originally scheduled. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the break was initially scheduled between March 22 and April 1.